ed by an abnormally elevated state of arousal, energy, and mood. It is often associated with bipolar disorder and is marked by hyperactivity, increased activity levels, and heightened emotional states. Individuals experiencing mania may exhibit impulsive behaviors, which can sometimes lead to harmful consequences. The condition requires specific care and monitoring, and it is commonly treated with medications such as lithium and antiepileptic drugs to manage symptoms and stabilize mood. Overall, mania is a complex and significant aspect of mental health that necessitates professional intervention and support."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}